Syphilis Project Update

Christian Testa

May 28th, 2019

In this project we are modeling syphilis in Louisiana and Massachusetts.

In each of these two states, we have calibrated the model and can use it to simulate hypothetical scenarios which may yield useful insight into effective health policy.

This document will walk readers through the background of the model, an analysis of hypothetical interventions, and our intentions for future developments.

Model Background

Data Being Used

Calibration targets include:

  • Reported Cases by Stage, Sex, Race
  • Proportion of Male Cases Among MSM
  • Proportion of Cases Among MSM with HIV Coinfection
  • Subpopulation Assortative Mixing (Age, Race)

Analysis of Interventions

The primary research question we have been investigating has been:

How do interventions which are focused on raising the baseline level of screening in the entire population compare to interventions targeted on men who have sex with men (MSM) populations?
